/**
 * CustomFunctions.groovy — Reusable utility functions for CPI message mappings.
 *
 * These replace common Java UDFs from PI/PO message mappings. In CPI, reference
 * these from a Groovy Script step placed before the mapping, or call them directly
 * from a Groovy mapping function.
 *
 * Categories:
 *   1. String manipulation (padding, trimming, case, encoding)
 *   2. Date/time conversion (PI/PO ↔ SAP ↔ ISO formats)
 *   3. Number formatting (leading zeros, decimal conversion)
 *   4. IDoc/BAPI helpers (segment handling, status codes)
 *   5. XML/JSON utilities (XPath extraction, namespace stripping)
 *   6. Lookup and default value handling
 *   7. Conditional mapping helpers (exists, coalesce, if-then-else)
 *
 * Generated by Sashay Control Tower for iFlow: {{ iflow_id }}
 */

